RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Lake Stevens, WA operates under a mayor-council system. The Mayor, Brett Gailey, was reelected in 2023. The City Council consists of seven members elected at-large. As of November 10, 2025, the listed council members are currently in office. However, recent election results from November 6, 2025, indicate that Sabina Araya is leading for Council Position 1, Brian McManus for Council Position 2, Tosha Edwards for Council Position 6, and Nathan Packard for Council Position 7. These results are pending certification on November 25, 2025.
